+### ALFRED-MF-028 — Cleanup artifact as doctrine
+```yaml
+id: ALFRED-MF-028
+status: accepted
+pattern: Cleanup prompt flows, proposal folders, or patch artifacts are treated as Alfred doctrine because they are recent or detailed.
+trigger_conditions:
+  - cleanup_patch_proposals are present
+  - handover diffs are stored under appendices
+  - process-control files contain strong wording
+countermeasure: Treat cleanup and proposal artifacts as process evidence only. Do not ingest them into ESSENCE, BEST_PRACTICES, MISTAKES, or TEMPLATES except as anti-drift controls.
+evidence_refs:
+  - appendices/APPENDIX_ALFRED_KB_CLEANUP_PROMPT_FLOW.md
+  - appendices/cleanup_patch_proposals/
+scores:
+  EVD: 80
+  IMP: 80
+  RSK: 70
+owner: alfred
+validator: meta_ops
+review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
